<p>
	Calendula flowers contain a variety of compounds which are believed to support wound healing and promote skin health. Topical uses of calendula ointment would be for cuts, scratches, grazes, acne, stretch marks and burns etc. Herbalists believe calendula is very versatile, may speed the healing of wounds and make the skin more supple by increasing the blood supply to it. This ointment can be used as a natural beauty face, hand or body rub or specifically on skin marks as a natural healing and repairing product. Very well known for use on stretch marks.<br />
	<br />
	Directions: this ointment can be used in both the morning and evening. A small amount of ointment should be applied to the affected areas.</p>
